description: Palindromes with exactly 4 palindromic prime factors (counted with multiplicity).
links: Lars Blomberg, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..320, terms < 10^16.
example: The palindrome 1596951 is a term since it has 4 factors 3^2 191 929, all palindromic.
author: _Patrick De Geest_, Jun 15 1998
